```
34.202.224.208  52.66.99.126   15.206.217.7   13.126.35.181  3.6.228.131
13.232.173.180  13.127.57.130  13.234.143.231 3.7.115.196    13.232.49.3
18.193.1.225    3.68.131.220   63.176.209.228 63.183.31.123   # added 2026-04-15
```
IPs change over time — keep them in config (`GUPSHUP_WEBHOOK_IPS`), not hardcoded, and re-check the docs periodically.

## 9. Templates (API-only — no manual portal authoring)

Gupshup Partner Portal does **not** provide a UI to create templates on the platform app.
Templates are created exclusively via API:

| Action | API |
|--------|-----|
| Apply / create | `POST /partner/app/{appId}/templates` (form-urlencoded: `elementName`, `category`, `content`, `example`, `vertical`, …) |
| List | `GET /partner/app/{appId}/templates` |
| Read one | `GET /partner/app/{appId}/templates/{templateId}` |
| Send | `POST /partner/app/{appId}/template/msg` with approved `template.id` |

**Shared platform number (multi-tenant):**

1. Configure the platform app (`GUPSHUP_PLATFORM_*` or Admin → Gupshup shared app).
2. **Admin → Platform → Template Manager**: create drafts, submit via API, sync status, link approved IDs to notification slots.
3. Wait for Meta approval (`PENDING` → `APPROVED`). Use **Sync** on each row or **Sync approved → slots** when ready.
4. Approved IDs populate `AdminSettings.notifications.whatsapp.templates.*` for transactional sends.

Salons with **their own connected app** use **WhatsApp → Templates** in the tenant UI (same API, their app via `resolveSender`).

- Categories: **`AUTHENTICATION`**, **`MARKETING`**, **`UTILITY`** only.
- Provide `example`/`exampleHeader` and `enableSample=true` (required for variable templates).
- Optional: Meta Library templates (`gettemplatesfromlibrary` → `createtemplatefromlibrary`) for pre-approved utility flows.
- Approval is async: status starts `PENDING`. Poll/sync with `GET .../templates`.
- Client: `backend/services/gupshup-whatsapp-service.js` (`applyTemplate`, `listTemplates`).
- Catalog: `backend/lib/gupshup-platform-template-catalog.js`.

## 10. Media management (partner responsibility)

- On inbound media: **download and store it yourself** (S3/GCS) immediately. Persist the **expiry timestamp**.
- Do **not** re-fetch media older than **7 days** (Cloud API) — it expires. Migrated on-prem→CAPI media will not work; never call it.
- Invalid media returns `400/404 {"status":"error","message":"Invalid Media Id"}`. **Use this to stop retrying.**
- **20+ invalid media calls/hour → `429` with a 1-hour cooldown.** Cache invalid IDs so you never re-request them.

## 11. Security (see also `security.mdc`)

- Secrets (`GUPSHUP_EMAIL`, `GUPSHUP_CLIENT_SECRET`, webhook shared secret) live in env / host secret store — document in `env.example` with placeholders, never real values.
- App Access Tokens & Partner Tokens: encrypt at rest (`lib/crypto.js`), decrypt only at call time, never log plaintext, never send to the client bundle.
- Webhook is a trust boundary: verify the shared-secret header **and** source IP; validate/sanitize every field server-side before persisting.
- Authorize mutating admin/config routes (who may connect/disconnect a WABA), not just authenticate.

## 12. Fitting this codebase

**Tenant CRM API routes (Gupshup WABA — primary paths):**

| Feature | Primary route | Legacy alias |
|---------|---------------|--------------|
| Connect / status | `/api/whatsapp/gupshup/*` | — |
| Templates | `/api/whatsapp/gupshup/templates/*` | `/api/whatsapp/v2/templates/*` |
| Campaigns | `/api/whatsapp/gupshup/campaigns/*` | `/api/whatsapp/v2/campaigns/*` |
| Inbox | `/api/whatsapp/gupshup/inbox/*` | `/api/whatsapp/v2/inbox/*` |
| Message reports | `/api/whatsapp/gupshup/messages/*` | `/api/whatsapp/v2/messages/*` |
| Tracking (tenant) | `GET /api/whatsapp/gupshup/messages/tracking` | — |
| Logs (tenant) | `GET /api/whatsapp/gupshup/messages/logs` | — |
| Test send (tenant) | `POST /api/whatsapp/gupshup/test-message` | — |
| Admin tracking | `GET /api/admin/gupshup/messages/tracking` | — |

**Platform admin:** `/api/admin/gupshup/*` (templates, campaigns, inbox, webhooks).

**MSG91 legacy** (transactional fallback analytics only): `/api/whatsapp/msg91/*` (alias `/api/whatsapp/*`).

When implementing, follow existing conventions:
- New provider client: `backend/services/gupshup-whatsapp-service.js` (token lookup, decrypt-at-use, axios, no plaintext logs).
- Register in `whatsapp-router.js` so `send-whatsapp.js` can route to it; keep dedupe + wallet debit in the unified pipeline.
- Per-business config on `WhatsAppAccount` (`provider: 'gupshup'`, `gupshupAppId`, `appTokenCipher`); shared platform app in env (`GUPSHUP_PLATFORM_*`) or AdminSettings (`gupshupAppId`, `gupshupSourceNumber`).
- Webhook route `backend/routes/gupshup-webhook.js`, mounted under the CSRF **skip** list (external POST, secret+IP verified instead — see `csrf.mdc`).
- Main DB is `ease_my_salon_main` via `databaseManager.getMainConnection()`.

